\begin{chessboard}[fen="rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1",
color={White="w", Black="b"}]
\end{chessboard}

In this example, the FEN code is specified as "rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1". The colors of the pieces are specified using the color={White="w", Black="b"} command.

To create a LaTeX code that contains all the necessary chess pieces, you can use the following code:

